src.predict.run(event, context)[source]

AWS Lambda handler function. Make a prediction using the trained model.

Parameters:

  • event –

    object containing the input data Expect the input to have a health_info key:

    ”health_info”{

    “HighBP”: , “HighChol”: , “CholCheck”:, “BMI”: , “Smoker”: , “Stroke”: , “HeartDiseaseorAttack”: , “PhysActivity”: , “Fruits”: , “Veggies” , “HvyAlcoholConsump”:, “AnyHealthcare”:, “NoDocbcCost”:, “GenHlth”:, “MentHlth”:, “PhysHlth”:, “DiffWalk”:, “Sex”:, “Age”:, “Education”: , “Income”:

    }

  • context – AWS Lambda context object

Returns:

prediction result (0.0 - no diabetes or 1.0 - prediabetes or diabetes)
